# Folder Structure

## Feature-based architecture

```
features/
  HomePage/
    index.tsx            ← orchestrator: state, Head, layout shell, section composition
    types.ts             ← shared types (InterestForm, etc.)
    sections/
      Navbar/
        index.tsx
        constants.ts     ← navItems[]
      Hero/
        index.tsx
        constants.ts     ← heroStats[]
      Partners/
        index.tsx
        constants.ts     ← partners[]
      About/
        index.tsx
        constants.ts     ← aboutPoints[], featureCards[]
      ProblemSolution/
        index.tsx        ← inline constants OK (small, not reused)
      Courses/
        index.tsx
        constants.ts     ← courseCategories[], programmeApproach[]
      HowItWorks/
        index.tsx
        constants.ts     ← steps[]
      IndustryModel/
        index.tsx
        constants.ts     ← modelPoints[], frameworkItems[], deliveryEcosystem[]
      Leadership/
        index.tsx
        constants.ts     ← leadership[]
      CTASection/
        index.tsx
      Contact/
        index.tsx
      Footer/
        index.tsx
      InterestDialog/
        index.tsx        ← MUI Dialog + form inputs

pages/
  index.tsx              ← thin wrapper: imports and renders <HomePage />
```

## Rules

- `pages/index.tsx` only imports and renders `<HomePage />` — no logic, no state
- All page-level state lives in `features/HomePage/index.tsx`
- Constants (static data arrays) always go in `constants.ts` next to the component
- Types shared across sections go in `features/HomePage/types.ts`
- Inline constants are OK only when: ≤ 3 items AND not reused elsewhere
- MUI icon imports belong in `constants.ts` when used as data (Icon components in arrays)

## Props pattern — pass handlers, not state

```tsx
// ✅ Pass handlers as props
<Navbar scrollToSection={scrollToSection} />
<Hero onShowInterest={() => setInterestOpen(true)} />
<CTASection scrollToSection={scrollToSection} />
```

## New pages follow the same pattern

```
features/
  SomePage/
    index.tsx
    types.ts
    sections/
      SectionName/
        index.tsx
        constants.ts
pages/
  some-page.tsx   ← just renders <SomePage />
```
